{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900718495,"sessionID":"ses_28413df37ffeJyWAcJXCOWZImd","part":{"id":"prt_d7bee7570001baYx224lTcLoOC","messageID":"msg_d7bed029f001gSounzqteXvyRm","sessionID":"ses_28413df37ffeJyWAcJXCOWZImd","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-68e57a1a17d64c76bd9af7fc58a1d455","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md","content":"# AgentCube Python SDK Tests — Design\n\nAR: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\nModule: sdk-python/tests\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Test Structure\n\n| File | Module Tested | Focus |\n|------|---------------|-------|\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | `agentcube.code_interpreter` | `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle, delegation |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.control_plane` | `ControlPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.code_interpreter_data_plane` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` API calls |\n| `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle, invoke |\n| `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` HTTP operations |\n| `test_agent_runtime_integration.py` | `agentcube.agent_runtime` | Full workflow integration tests |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | `agentcube.exceptions` | Exception hierarchy validation |\n| `test_utils.py` | `agentcube.utils.*` | Utility functions |\n| `test_exports.py` | `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Public API surface validation |\n\n### Test Categories\n\n1. **Unit Tests** — Mock HTTP responses, test single class/method behavior\n2. **Integration Tests** — Test component interactions with mock backend\n3. **Contract Tests** — Verify HTTP request/response format matches spec\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n\n- `responses` library for HTTP mocking (wire-level interception)\n- `unittest.mock` for patching internal dependencies\n- `pytest-mock` for fixture-based mock injection\n- `MagicMock` for response objects when testing client internals\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Mock Response Data\n\n#### Control Plane Responses\n\n```python\n# create_session success\n{\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n\n# create_session failure (missing sessionId)\n{}\n\n# delete_session success\n# HTTP 200 or 404 (both treated as success)\n```\n\n#### Code Interpreter Data Plane Responses\n\n```python\n# execute_command success\n{\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"}\n\n# execute_command failure\n{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error message\"}\n\n# list_files\n{\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n```\n\n#### Agent Runtime Responses\n\n```python\n# bootstrap (GET) — headers only\n# Response headers: {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n\n# invoke (POST)\n{\"result\": \"success\"}\n{\"output\": \"processed\", \"status\": \"completed\"}\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```python\n# tmp_path fixture (pytest built-in) for file operations\nlocal_file = tmp_path / \"test.txt\"\nlocal_file.write_text(\"content\")\n\n# Environment isolation\nos.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = \"http://router\"\nos.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"] = \"http://wm\"\n# Cleanup after test\ndel os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"]\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Control Plane Client Tests (`test_control_plane.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestControlPlaneClientInit` | Default/custom timeout | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` defaults |\n| `TestAuthTokenResolution` | Explicit/file/env | Token resolution order: arg → file → none |\n| `TestURLResolution` | Explicit/env/required | URL resolution order: arg → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` → raise |\n| `TestCreateSession` | Success/missing ID/metadata | `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, JSON body format |\n| `TestDeleteSession` | Success/404/failure | `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`, 404 = success |\n| `TestClose` | Session cleanup | `session.close()` called |\n\n### Code Interpreter Data Plane Tests (`test_data_plane.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestDataPlaneClientInit` | session_id/base_url/params | Constructor parameter requirements |\n| `TestSessionHeader` | Header lowercase | `x-agentcube-session-id` header on session |\n| `TestBaseURLConstruction` | URL from router | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr}/invocations/` |\n| `TestExecuteCommand` | Success/list input/timeout buffer | `POST api/execute`, JSON body, timeout+2s buffer |\n| `TestWriteFile` | base64/mode | `POST api/files`, base64 content, `\"0644\"` mode |\n| `TestUploadFile` | multipart/session header | `POST api/files` multipart, explicit session header |\n| `TestDownloadFile` | stream/parent dir/slash strip | `GET api/files/{path}`, `stream=True`, leading slash removal |\n| `TestListFiles` | query/default path | `GET api/files`, `params={\"path\": ...}` |\n\n### Code Interpreter Client Tests (`test_code_interpreter.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClientInit` | URL required/env/explicit | `ROUTER_URL` env or arg required |\n| `TestSessionCreation` | Created/reused | `create_session` called when no `session_id` |\n| `TestContextManager` | Normal exit/exception | `__exit__` calls `stop()` always |\n| `TestStopMethod` | Cleanup/conditional delete | Data plane close, control plane delete only if created |\n| `TestExecuteCommandDelegation` | Pass-through | `execute_command` delegates to `_dp_client` |\n| `TestRunCode` | Python language | Write `.py` file, execute `python3 <file>` |\n| `TestFileOperations` | write/list | Delegation to data plane methods |\n| `TestVerboseMode` | Logger level | `DEBUG` when verbose, `INFO` otherwise |\n| `TestDataPlaneInitFailure` | Cleanup on failure | `delete_session` called if data plane init fails |\n\n### Agent Runtime Client Tests (`test_agent_runtime_client.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClientInit` | All params | Parameter storage |\n| `TestRouterURLRequired` | Required validation | `ROUTER_URL` or arg required |\n| `TestRouterURLResolution` | Env/explicit | Resolution order |\n| `TestSessionReuse` | Provided session_id | No bootstrap GET when `session_id` provided |\n| `TestSessionBootstrap` | GET bootstrap | `GET` base invocation URL for session header |\n| `TestDataPlaneInit` | dp_client creation | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instantiated |\n| `TestContextManager` | enter/exit/exception | `close()` called on exit |\n| `TestInvoke` | delegation/without session | `dp_client.invoke` called, error if no session |\n| `TestClose` | data plane close | `dp_client.close()` called |\n\n### Agent Runtime Data Plane Tests (`test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestDataPlaneClientInit` | Default/custom timeout | Timeout defaults |\n| `TestSessionHeaderConstant` | Value check | `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n| `TestBaseURLConstruction` | URL format | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` |\n| `TestConnectionPooling` | HTTPAdapter | `HTTPAdapter` mounted for http/https |\n| `TestBootstrapSessionID` | success/missing header | `GET` base URL, header extraction, error if missing |\n| `TestInvoke` | with session | `POST` base URL, JSON body |\n| `TestInvokeHeaders` | headers correctness | `x-agentcube-session-id` + `Content-Type: application/json` |\n| `TestInvokeTimeout` | override/default | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple |\n\n### Integration Tests (`test_agent_runtime_integration.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestSessionLifecycle` | Full workflow | Bootstrap → invoke → close |\n| `TestInvokeWorkflow` | Payload processing | POST with payload, response parsing |\n| `TestSessionReuseIntegration` | Multiple invokes | Same session across multiple calls |\n| `TestBootstrapFailure` | Missing header error | ValueError raised |\n| `TestInvokeFailure` | HTTP error | `requests.HTTPError` raised |\n\n### Utils Tests (`test_utils.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestCreateSession` | Returns/adapters/custom pool | `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` |\n| `TestReadTokenFromFile` | success/not found/strip/multiline | File read, strip, empty on missing |\n| `TestGetLogger` | Returns/default level/custom level | `logging.Logger`, `INFO` default, level config |\n\n### Exception Tests (`test_exceptions.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestExceptionHierarchy` | Inheritance | All inherit from `AgentCubeError` |\n| `TestCommandExecutionError` | Constructor/message | `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`, message format |\n| `TestSessionError` | Docstring/inheritance | Docstring contains \"session\" |\n| `TestDataPlaneError` | Docstring/inheritance | Docstring contains \"data plane\" |\n\n### Export Tests (`test_exports.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenario | Contract Verified |\n|------------|----------|-------------------|\n| `TestRootPackageExports` | Import/`__all__` | Only `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `TestClientsPackageExports` | Import/`__all__` | `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Types Tested\n\n| Exception | Raised When | Test Coverage |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| `ValueError` | Missing required config (router_url, workload_manager_url, sessionId) | All client init tests |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command non-zero exit | `test_data_plane.py::TestExecuteCommand::test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` |\n| `FileNotFoundError` | Upload local file not found | `test_data_plane.py::TestUploadFile::test_upload_file_not_found` |\n| `requests.HTTPError` | HTTP failure (non-2xx) | Integration tests with `status=500` |\n| `RuntimeError` | Data plane client not initialized | `CodeInterpreterClient` methods |\n\n### Error Message Patterns\n\n```python\n# Config errors\n\"router_url must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n\"workload_manager_url must be provided via argument or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n\"sessionId not found in create_session response\"\n\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n\n# Execution errors\n\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n\"Unsupported language: {language}. Supported: python, py, python3\"\n\"Either base_url or router_url, namespace, and cr_name must be provided\"\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Pyramid\n\n```\n     ┌─────────────┐\n     │ Integration │  ← test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n     │    (6)      │     Full workflow with mock backend\n     ├─────────────┤\n     │   Contract  │  ← HTTP request/response format tests\n     │    (15)     │     within each test file\n     ├─────────────┤\n     │    Unit     │  ← Most tests (mocked internals)\n     │   (100+)    │     Isolated class/method tests\n     └─────────────┘\n```\n\n### Mock Levels\n\n1. **Wire-level** — `responses` intercepts actual HTTP calls\n   - Used for: HTTP contract tests, integration tests\n   - Example: `responses.post(\"http://wm/v1/code-interpreter\", json={\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"})`\n\n2. **Object-level** — `MagicMock` replaces response objects\n   - Used for: Testing client internals without HTTP\n   - Example: `mock_response.json.return_value = {\"exit_code\": 0}`\n\n3. **Dependency-level** — `patch` replaces entire classes\n   - Used for: Testing failure paths, cleanup behavior\n   - Example: `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client)`\n\n### Coverage Goals\n\n| Module | Target Coverage | Current Tests |\n|--------|-----------------|---------------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | 100% (exports only) | `test_exports.py` |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | 95%+ | `test_code_interpreter.py` (296 lines) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | 95%+ | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` + `test_agent_runtime_integration.py` |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_control_plane.py` (169 lines) |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_data_plane.py` (338 lines) |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95%+ | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` (178 lines) |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | 100% | `test_exceptions.py` (66 lines) |\n| `agentcube/utils/*.py` | 95%+ | `test_utils.py` (71 lines) |\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\npytest sdk-python/tests/ -v\n\n# Run with coverage\npytest sdk-python/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Run specific module\npytest sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n\n# Run specific test\npytest sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestContextManager::test_context_manager_calls_stop\n```\n\n### CI Integration\n\n- `pytest.ini_options` configured in `pyproject.toml`\n- `addopts = \"-v --tb=short\"` for verbose output with short traceback\n- Coverage excludes: `pragma: no cover`, `__repr__`, `NotImplementedError`, `__main__`\n\n### Key Test Patterns\n\n1. **Parameter Validation**\n   ```python\n   def test_router_url_required(self) -> None:\n       if \"ROUTER_URL\" in os.environ:\n           del os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"]\n       with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n           CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n   ```\n\n2. **Delegation Testing**\n   ```python\n   def test_execute_command_delegates_to_data_plane(self) -> None:\n       # Setup mock response\n       responses.post(..., json={\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"})\n       client = CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n       result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n       assert result == \"output\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Cleanup Verification**\n   ```python\n   def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleans_up_session(self) -> None:\n       mock_cp_client.delete_session = Mock(return_value=True)\n       with patch(...):\n           with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n               CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n       mock_cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once_with(\"session-123\")\n   ```\n\n4. **HTTP Contract Testing**\n   ```python\n   def test_execute_command_json_body(self) -> None:\n       client.execute_command(\"python3 script.py\", timeout=30)\n       call_args = client._request.call_args\n       body = json.loads(call_args.args[2].decode())\n       assert body[\"command\"] == [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n       assert body[\"timeout\"] == \"30s\"\n   ```\n\n5. **Integration Workflow**\n   ```python\n   @responses.activate\n   def test_full_session_lifecycle(self):\n       responses.get(..., headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"})\n       responses.post(..., json={\"result\": \"success\"})\n       with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:\n           assert client.session_id == \"session-123\"\n           result = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})\n           assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n   ```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",       # Test framework\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\", # Mock fixtures\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.0.0\",   # Coverage plugin\n    \"responses>=0.23.0\",   # HTTP mocking\n]\n```\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **E2E Tests** — Add tests that run against real backend (marked with `@pytest.mark.e2e`)\n2. **Performance Tests** — Add timeout behavior tests with actual delay simulation\n3. **Error Recovery Tests** — Add tests for retry behavior (if implemented)\n4. **Multi-language Tests** — Expand `run_code` tests for additional languages beyond Python"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_integration.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_exports.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/design.md","time":{"start":1775900718481,"end":1775900718492}}}}
